{{Quote|It's a countersurveillance technique. The Jedi use it to temporarily blind security cams and intrusion alarms. On the vids, it looks like a minor glitch.|[[Jagged Fel]]|<ref name="Apocalypse">''[[Fate of the Jedi: Apocalypse]]''</ref>}}
The '''Force-flash''', also spelled '''Force flash''', was a [[Force power/Legends|Force power]] that prevented the user from being detected by others.<ref name="Apocalypse" /> The user could temporarily "'''fuzz'''"&mdash;disable&mdash;a security [[Holocamera/Legends|holocam]] through [[The Force/Legends|the Force]], causing a brief period of static, allowing the user to pass while only alerting security to a minor holocam malfunction.<ref name="Outcast">''[[Fate of the Jedi: Outcast]]''</ref> Another usage of the Force under the same name allowed the [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-user]] to produce an unnatural flash of bright light, temporary blinding their opponents.

[[Seff Hellin]] used Force flash on the [[Armand Isard Correctional Facility]]'s holocams during his [[Raid on the Armand Isard Correctional Facility|raid]] on it.<ref name="Outcast" /> [[Abeloth]] was capable of producing a flash powerful enough to affect the visuals of ships across the entire [[Exodo system/Legends|Exodo system]].<ref name="Apocalypse" />

[[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] was alleged to be able to use this power by [[Tahiri Veila]].<ref name="Apocalypse" />

